15/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The foreign ministry announced on Wednesday (14 May) that the country would provide ammunition and military equipment to Afghanistan in accordance with a government decree issued in September.
It will be the third and final shipment under a support programme offered to Afghanistan's national army.
Croatia also participates in the International Security Assistance Force with a military police platoon.
Also Wednesday, the UN and the defence ministry launched a training course for military instructors in Rakitje, near Zagreb.
Croatian officers, UN peacekeeping instructors and military personnel from 21 countries are participating.
(HINA, HRT - 14/05/03)
